						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikramachōḻa. Year 14: A.D. 1132.</hi></p>						

						<p>Unfinished and much damaged. Beginning lost and built in at the end. The last portion is left un-engraved. The beginning portion and some parts in the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> commencing with <hi rend="italic">Pūmādu puṇara</hi> of the Chōḻa king, Vikramachōḻa I are lost. Records several assignments of sheep to shepherds, probably for supplying ghee to the temple for lighting lamps. Some of the recipients are Tiruchchiṟṟabalak-kōn, Kōdaṇḍan Pañchanadi, Āraṭṭamudak-kōn, and Ārūr Nambi. Mentions Peru Milaṭṭūr in Kiḻāṟkūṟṟam, a subdivision of Nittaviṉōda-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
